---
const tiers = [
  {
    tier: "T01",
    role: "Authority Architect",
    name: "Platte F. Clark",
    rate: "275",
    bio: "Lead writer and book architect for category-defining titles. WGA member. Big Five novelist. Lionsgate-credited screenwriter. Twenty-five years building behavior-change curriculum for FranklinCovey, VitalSmarts, ZengerFolkman, and global organizations across four continents.",
    accent: true,
  },
  {
    tier: "T02",
    role: "Production Writer",
    name: "Kennidy Clark",
    rate: "125",
    bio: "Production drafting under Platte's direct supervision. A younger voice for younger audiences, sharp on contemporary register, and the right fit for authors with leaner budgets who still need the Straw Dogs architectural standard on the manuscript.",
    accent: false,
  },
];
---

<section id="team" class="border-t border-rule py-20 sm:py-28 px-6 fade-in">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="mb-14 sm:mb-16 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">/ The Team</p>
      <h2 class="display text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl leading-[1.05] mb-6" style="font-weight: 500;">
        Two <span class="display-italic" style="font-weight: 500;">tiers</span>.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-bone-soft leading-relaxed text-lg">
        Senior ghostwriters typically price out every author except those with the largest budgets.
        Our structure solves that. Many projects use both tiers in combination&mdash;Platte for
        architecture, structural editorial, voice, and specific narrative challenges; Kennidy for
        production drafting under his direct supervision. Publishers can match the right blend to
        each author's budget without compromising the book that ends up on your imprint.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5 lg:gap-6">
      {tiers.map((t) => (
        <div class={`${t.accent ? 'surface-glow' : 'surface'} rounded-sm p-7 sm:p-9`}>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <span class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.18em] copper">{t.tier}</span>
            <span class="copper-rule flex-1 opacity-40"></span>
            <span class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.14em] uppercase text-bone-mute">{t.role}</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="display text-3xl sm:text-4xl mb-2 text-bone leading-tight" style="font-weight: 500;">
            {t.name}
          </h3>
          <div class="flex items-baseline gap-1.5 mb-7">
            <span class="display text-5xl sm:text-6xl tracking-tight" style="font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-copper-bright);">
              ${t.rate}
            </span>
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-bone-mute">/hour</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-bone-soft leading-relaxed text-[0.95rem]">{t.bio}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
